==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*tīði-'': cognate with Old Saxon ''tīd'' (Dutch [[tijd]]), Old High German [[zit|zīt]] (German [[Zeit]]), Old Norse [[tíð]] (Swedish [[tid#Swedish|tid]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ti:d/}}

===Noun===
{{Unicode|'''tīd'''}} ''f'' (plural {{Unicode|'''[[tida|tīda]]'''}} or {{Unicode|'''[[tide|tīde]]'''}}; accusative {{Unicode|'''[[tide|tīde]]'''}} or {{Unicode|'''tīd'''}})
# [[time]]: an interval of time, a specific period
# an [[hour]]
# a [[season]]
# a specific point in time
# a feast-day

